## Relation to `coding_style.mdc`

| Topic | `coding_style.mdc` (tutorial scripts) | This rule (globs above) |
|--------|----------------------------------------|-------------------------|
| Pipe | **`%>%`** encouraged for tidyverse | **`|>`** native pipe |
| Comments | Frequent, educational | Still clear; avoid noise |
| `library(tidyverse)` | Broad tidyverse preference | **Explicit `library()`** per file |
| Row-wise logic | Some one-line `if` examples | **Vectorized** `mutate` / `case_when` / **stringr** |
| Assignment | **`=`** | **`=`** only (never **`<-`**); [arrows.mdc](arrows.mdc) |

When both rules could apply, **this rule wins for R files under the globs**; use **coding_style.mdc** for `LAB_*` / `READ_*` / `ACTIVITY_*` materials and other tutorial paths not covered here.
